# Firebase Deployment Ignore Rules
# These rules apply to the directory specified in firebase.json "hosting.public" (usually "dist" or "public")

# Ignore known large content/generated directories
# Even if these end up in 'dist' via Vite, we tell Firebase NOT to upload them.
showcase/
public/showcase/
generated/
outputs/
tmp/
models/

# Ignore source files if they accidentally get copied
src/
node_modules/
.git/
.gitignore
firebase.json
.firebaserc
.firebaseignore
README.md
*.log

# OPTIONAL: Aggressive Image Blocking
# Uncomment the lines below if you want to strictly prevent ANY images from being hosted.
# WARNING: This will break app icons and UI assets compiled into 'dist/assets' unless you whitelist them.
# **/*.png
# **/*.jpg
# **/*.webp
# **/*.gif

# If you use the aggressive blocking above, whitelist your UI assets like this:
# !assets/**
# !vite.svg
